      "content": "I understand your desperation, but combining even a small dose of melatonin with zolpidem can still increase the risk of side effects such as excessive drowsiness, dizziness, and confusion. It's important to remember that even a tiny bit can have a significant impact, especially when combined with a prescription sleep aid. I would strongly recommend taking either melatonin or zolpidem at separate times, and exploring other non-pharmacological methods to improve your sleep, such as cognitive-behavioral therapy for insomnia (CBT-I) or relaxation techniques. Your doctor can help you find the safest and most effective way to address your sleep issues without the added risk of combining these medications.",
